'''Comal (cookware)'''
# Flat metal cookware used in Mexican homes to cook tortillas and toast bread. It is more similar to a pan than a toaster. 

Uses of comales (plural form) include warming tortillas for burritos or in preparation for quesadillas (tortillas with cheese).

